16 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
17 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
18 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 3314.1 of Title 70, unless there
19 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
20 A. The Board of Regents of the University of Oklahoma is hereby
21 authorized to establish within the College of Education at the
22 University of Oklahoma a pilot program to provide high-dosage
23 mathematics tutoring for the lowest performing ninth-grade students
24 resulting from the required eighth-grade mathematics assessment
HB1287 HFLR Page 1
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.
1 prov ided for in Section 1210.508 of Title 70 of the Oklahoma
2 Statutes.
3 B. The pilot program described in subsection A of this section
4 shall run for public high schools in districts with thirty thousand
5 (30,000) enrolled students or greater, as well as public charter
6 schools established pursuant to the Oklahoma Charter School Act.
7 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2025.
8 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
9 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
10 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
11 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
12
